#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:1
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:3
msgid "Choosing an Instance"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:5
msgid ""
"If you are used to sites like Reddit, then Lemmy works in a fundamentally "
"different way. Instead of a single website like reddit.com, there are many "
"different websites (called _instances_). These are operated by different "
"people, have different topics and rules. Nevertheless, posts created in one "
"instance can directly be seen by users who are registered on another. Its "
"basically like email, but for social media."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:7
msgid ""
"This means before using Lemmy and registering an account, you need to pick "
"an instance. For this you can browse the instance list and look for one that "
"matches your topics of interest. You can also see if the rules match your "
"expectations, and how many users there are. It is better to avoid very big "
"or very small instances. But don't worry too much about this choice, you can "
"always create another account on a different instance later."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:9
msgid "[**Instance List**](https://join-lemmy.org/instances)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:11
msgid "Registration"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:13
msgid ""
"Once you choose an instance, it's time to create your account. To do this, "
"click _sign up_ in the top right of the page, or click the top right button "
"on mobile to open a menu with _sign up_ link."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:15
msgid "On the signup page you need to enter a few things:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:17
msgid ""
"**Username**: How do you want to be called? This name can not be changed and "
"is unique within an instance. Later you can also set a _displayname_ which "
"can be freely changed. If your desired username is taken, consider choosing "
"a different instance where it is still available."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:18
msgid ""
"**Email**: Your email address. This is used for password resets and "
"notifications (if enabled). Providing an email address is usually optional, "
"but admins may choose to make it mandatory. In this case you will have to "
"wait for a confirmation mail and click the link after completing this form."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:19
msgid ""
"**Password**: The password for logging in to your account. Make sure to "
"choose a long and unique password which isn't used on any other website."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:20
msgid ""
"**Verify password**: Repeat the same password from above to ensure that it "
"was entered correctly."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:22
msgid ""
"There are also a few optional fields, which you may need to fill in "
"depending on the instance configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:24
msgid ""
"**Question/Answer**: Instance admins can set an arbitrary question which "
"needs to be answered in order to create an account. This is often used to "
"prevent spam bots from signing up. After submitting the form, you will need "
"to wait for some time until the answer is approved manually before you can "
"login."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:25
msgid ""
"**Code**: A captcha which is easy to solve for humans but hard for bots. "
"Enter the letters and numbers that you see in the text box, ignoring "
"uppercase or lowercase. Click the refresh button if you are unable to read a "
"character. The _play_ button plays an audio version of the captcha."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:26
msgid ""
"**Show NSFW content**: Here you can choose if content that is \"not safe for "
"work\" (or adult-only) should be shown."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:28
msgid "When you are done, press the _sign up_ button."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:30
msgid ""
"It depends on the instance configuration when you can login and start using "
"the account. In case the email is mandatory, you need to wait for the "
"confirmation email and click the link first. In case \"Question/Answer\" is "
"present, you need to wait for an admin to manually review and approve your "
"registration. If you have problems with the registration, try to get in "
"contact with the admin for support. You can also choose a different instance "
"to sign up if your primary choice does not work."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:32
msgid "Following Communities"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:34
msgid ""
"After logging in to your new account, its time to follow communities that "
"you are interested in. For this you can click on the _communities_ link at "
"the top of the page (on mobile, you need to click the menu icon on the top "
"right first). You will see a list of communities which can be filtered by "
"subscribed, local or all. Local communities are those which are hosted on "
"the same site where you are signed in, while _all_ also contains federated "
"communities from other instances. In any case you can directly subscribe to "
"communities with the right-hand subscribe link. Or click on the community "
"name to browse the community first, see what its posted and what the rules "
"are before subscribing."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:36
msgid ""
"Another way to find communities to subscribe to is by going to the front "
"page and browsing the posts. If there is something that interests you, click "
"on the post title to see more details and comments. Here you can subscribe "
"to the community in the right-hand sidebar, or by clicking the \"sidebar\" "
"button on mobile."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:38
msgid ""
"These previous ways will only show communities that are already known to the "
"instance. Especially if you joined a small or inactive Lemmy instance, there "
"will be few communities to discover. You can find more communities by "
"browsing different Lemmy instances, or using the [Lemmy Explorer](https://"
"lemmyverse.net/communities). When you found a community that you want to "
"follow, enter its URL (e.g. `https://feddit.org/c/main`) or the identifier "
"(e.g. `!main@feddit.org`) into the search field of your own Lemmy instance. "
"Lemmy will then fetch the community from its original instance, and allow "
"you to interact with it. The same method also works to fetch users, posts or "
"comments from other instances."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:40
msgid "Setting up Your Profile"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:42
msgid ""
"Before you start posting, its a good idea to provide some details about "
"yourself. Open the top-right menu and go to \"settings\". Here the following "
"settings are available for your public profile:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:44
msgid ""
"**Displayname**: An alternative username which can be changed at any time"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:45
msgid "**Bio**: Long description of yourself, can be formatted with Markdown"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:46
msgid ""
"**Matrix User**: Your username on the decentralized [Matrix chat](https://"
"matrix.org/)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:47
msgid "**Avatar**: Profile picture that is shown next to all your posts"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:48
msgid "**Banner**: A header image for your profile page"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:50
msgid ""
"On this page you can also change the email and password. Additionally there "
"are many other settings available, which allow customizing of your browsing "
"experience:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:52
msgid ""
"**Blocks** (tab at top of the page): Here you can block users and "
"communities, so that their posts will be hidden."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:53
msgid "**Interface language**: Which language the user interface should use."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:54
msgid ""
"**Languages**: Select the languages that you speak to see only content in "
"these languages. This is a new feature and many posts don't specify a "
"language yet, so be sure to select \"Undetermined\" to see them."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:55
msgid ""
"**Theme**: You can choose between different color themes for the user "
"interface. Instance admins can add more themes."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:56
msgid ""
"**Type**: Which timeline you want to see by default on the front page; only "
"posts from communities that you subscribe to, posts in local communities, or "
"all posts including federated."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:57
msgid ""
"**Sort type**: How posts and comments should be sorted by default. See "
"[Votes and Ranking](03-votes-and-ranking.md) for details."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:58
msgid ""
"**Show NSFW content**: Whether or not you want to see content that is \"not "
"safe for work\" (or adult-only)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:59
msgid ""
"**Show Scores**: Whether the number of upvotes and downvotes should be "
"visible."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:60
msgid ""
"**Show Avatars**: Whether profile pictures of other users should be shown."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:61
msgid ""
"**Bot Account**: Enable this if you are using a script or program to create "
"posts automatically"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:62
msgid ""
"**Show Bot Accounts**: Disable this to hide posts that were created by bot "
"accounts."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:63
msgid ""
"**Show Read Posts**: If this is disabled, posts that you already viewed are "
"not shown in listings anymore. Useful if you want to find new content "
"easily, but makes it difficult to follow ongoing discussion under existing "
"posts."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:64
msgid ""
"**Show Notifications for New Posts**: Enable this to receive a popup "
"notification for each new post that is created."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:65
msgid ""
"**Send notifications to Email**: Enable to receive notifications about new "
"comment replies and private messages to your email address."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:67
msgid "Start Posting"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:69
msgid ""
"Finally its time to start posting! To do this it is always a good idea to "
"read the community rules in the sidebar (below the _Subscribe_ button). When "
"you are ready, go to a post and type your comment in the box directly below "
"for a top-level reply. You can also write a nested reply to an existing "
"comment, by clicking the left-pointing arrow."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:71
msgid ""
"Other than commenting on existing posts, you can also create new posts. To "
"do this, click the button _Create a post_ in the sidebar. Here you can "
"optionally supply an external link or upload an image. The title field is "
"mandatory and should describe what you are posting. The body is again "
"optional, and gives space for long texts. You can also embed additional "
"images here. The _Community_ dropdown below allows choosing a different "
"community to post in. With _NSFW_, posts can be marked as \"not safe for "
"work\". Finally you can specify the language that the post is written in, "
"and then click on _Create_."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/01-getting-started.md:73
msgid ""
"One more possibility is to write private messages to individual users. To do "
"this, simply visit a user profile and click _Send message_. You will be "
"notified about new private messages and comment replies with the bell icon "
"in the top right."
msgstr ""
